# Backend API Documentation

This document details all available API endpoints, their expected request data (Body, Params, Query), and required headers.

## Base URL
All endpoints are prefixed with `/api`.

---

## 1. Authentication (`/api/auth`)

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Request Data (Body/Params) |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `POST` | `/send-otp` | Request a login OTP | **Body**: `{ phone: string }` |
| `POST` | `/verify-otp` | Verify OTP and login | **Body**: `{ phone: string, otp: string }` |
| `POST` | `/register` | Register a new user | **Body**: `{ name, email, password, phone, role_id }` |
| `POST` | `/login` | Login with credentials | **Body**: `{ email, password }` |
| `POST` | `/forgot-password`| Reset password trigger | **Body**: `{ email: string }` |

---

## 2. Admin Management (`/api/admin`)
*Requires `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header.*

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Request Data |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `GET` | `/users` | List all users | N/A |
| `PUT` | `/update-role` | Change user role | **Body**: `{ id: number, role: string }` |
| `DELETE` | `/delete-user/:id` | Remove a user | **Params**: `id` |
| `GET` | `/categories` | List categories | **Query**: Filter fields (optional) |
| `POST` | `/categories/add` | Add category | **Body**: Metadata; **Files**: `category_image_file`, `banner_image_file` |
| `PUT` | `/categories/update/:id` | Update category | **Params**: `id`; **Body**: Fields; **Files**: Image files |
| `DELETE`| `/categories/delete/:id` | Delete category | **Params**: `id` |
| `GET` | `/orders` | Fetch orders | N/A |
| `PUT` | `/orders/update-status`| Update order status | **Body**: Status update details |

---

## 3. Product Management (`/api/products`)
*Requires `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header.*

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Request Data |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | : :--- |
| `GET` | `/` | List all products | **Query**: `{ name: string }` (optional) |
| `POST` | `/add` | Add new product | **Body**: Metadata; **Files**: `product_image_file`, `image2_file`, `image3_file` |
| `PUT` | `/update/:id` | Update product | **Params**: `id`; **Body**: Fields; **Files**: Product images |
| `DELETE`| `/delete/:id` | Delete product | **Params**: `id` |

---

## 4. System

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Request Data |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `GET` | `/health` | Health check | N/A |

> [!NOTE]
> For `multipart/form-data` requests (adding products/categories), ensure you use the exact file field names listed above to ensure successful image processing.
